<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,703,1327]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,328,741,767]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species is distinguishable from the other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1057,1236,741,766]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Dendryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1057,1236,741,766]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Dendryphantes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Chile as the cephalothorax is black with large white areas made of white pennate hairs below and behind PLE. The abdomen is black with two transversal fawn stripes and a border of white hairs around the edge of the anterior two thirds of the abdomen. Tibia 
<number box="[541,556,853,879]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
has a clear white ventral fringe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,703,1327]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,424,890,916]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description: Male</emphasis>
(after 
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Leitao" box="[503,729,890,916]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. de (1936) Etude sur les Arachnides de Papudo et Constitucion (Chili), recueillis par le Prof. Dr Carlos E. Porter. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural, 40, 112 - 129." type="journal article" year="1936">
Mello-Leitao 
<number box="[665,729,890,916]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1936.0">1936</number>
</bibRefCitation>
): Cephalothorax black with large white areas made of white pennate hairs below and behind PLE. Chelicerae, endites, labium and anterior-tapering sternum are black. Abdomen black with two transversal fawn stripes and a border of white hairs around the edge of the anterior two thirds of the abdomen (
<bibRefCitation author="Mello-Leitao" box="[480,792,1002,1028]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. de (1936) Etude sur les Arachnides de Papudo et Constitucion (Chili), recueillis par le Prof. Dr Carlos E. Porter. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural, 40, 112 - 129." type="journal article" year="1936">
Mello-Leitao 
<number box="[645,707,1002,1028]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1936.0">1936</number>
, 
<figureCitation box="[720,792,1002,1028]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 10" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[170,1423,217,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,197,1860]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 10. Admesturius bitaeniatus. 4 – 5 dorsal view (4 female, 5 male); 6 – 7 female genitalia (6 dorsal view of cleared specimen, 7 ventral view of external characteristics); 8 – 9 male palp (8 ventral view, 9 lateral view); 10 known distribution. Scales: total body 1 mm; remainder 0.2 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194415/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[775,792,1002,1028]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
). Reflective hairs are scattered across the anterior and centre parts of the abdomen. The spinnerets are black. LI fringed, longer and much more robust than the other legs. All femurs and patellas plus tibias I to III black. Metatarsus I black. Metatarsi II to IV and basal part of patella IV fawn. All tarsi yellow with black hairs. Tibia I with a clear white ventral fringe. 
<emphasis box="[1247,1313,1115,1140]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Palp:</emphasis>
tibia with single small apophysis curved inwards and directed forward, embolus long, straight and solidly built (Mello- 
<bibRefCitation author="Leitao" box="[151,294,1189,1215]" pageId="18" pageNumber="48" refString="Mello-Leitao, C. F. de (1936) Etude sur les Arachnides de Papudo et Constitucion (Chili), recueillis par le Prof. Dr Carlos E. Porter. Revista Chilena de Historia Natural, 40, 112 - 129." type="journal article" year="1936">
Leitao 
<number box="[233,294,1189,1215]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1936.0">1936</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[306,392,1189,1215]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 10" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[170,1423,217,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,197,1860]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 10. Admesturius bitaeniatus. 4 – 5 dorsal view (4 female, 5 male); 6 – 7 female genitalia (6 dorsal view of cleared specimen, 7 ventral view of external characteristics); 8 – 9 male palp (8 ventral view, 9 lateral view); 10 known distribution. Scales: total body 1 mm; remainder 0.2 mm" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194415/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[359,392,1189,1215]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tegulum rounded, without lobe and partly divided distally. Ventral spines: T 
<number box="[1308,1319,1189,1215]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[1325,1338,1189,1215]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
- 
<number box="[1351,1364,1189,1215]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
- 
<number box="[1376,1389,1189,1215]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
, T 
<number box="[1422,1436,1189,1215]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[151,163,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
- 
<number box="[173,215,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1-2</number>
, M 
<number box="[259,269,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.0">1</number>
&amp; M 
<number box="[334,348,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[355,371,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
- 
<number box="[380,396,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
, T 
<number box="[428,441,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="3.0">3</number>
and T 
<number box="[516,531,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="4.0">4</number>
<number box="[538,554,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
- 
<number box="[563,579,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
, M 
<number box="[620,633,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="3.0">3</number>
and M 
<number box="[716,730,1226,1252]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="4.0">4</number>
with a distal circle of spines.
</paragraph>
